    <div class="article-body">

      <h2>National organizations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://ffrf.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Freedom From Religion Foundation</a></strong> — Chapters in most US states. Legal advocacy for church-state separation.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://americanhumanist.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Humanist Association</a></strong> — Local chapters and certified humanist celebrants nationwide.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.atheists.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Atheists</a></strong> — State directors and affiliate organizations across the US.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://centerforinquiry.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Center for Inquiry</a></strong> — Community groups promoting science and secularism.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.secular.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Secular Coalition for America</a></strong> — State chapters advocating for secular government.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>International</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.humanistsinternational.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Humanists International</a></strong> — Global umbrella for 170+ humanist organizations in 70+ countries.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://humanists.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Humanists UK</a></strong> — Britain's leading humanist organization.</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.rationalistinternational.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Rationalist International</a></strong> — Network promoting rationalism worldwide.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Online communities</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/atheism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/atheism</a></strong> — 2M+ members discussing secular perspectives</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/freethought/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/freethought</a></strong> — Curated freethought discussion</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/humanism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/humanism</a></strong> — Secular humanist community</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/DebateReligion/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">r/DebateReligion</a></strong> — Structured debate on religious claims</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Find local groups</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/topics/atheism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Atheist Meetups</a></strong> — Local gatherings worldwide</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/topics/humanism/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Humanist Meetups</a></strong> — Discussion groups and social events</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.meetup.com/topics/skeptics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Skeptics Meetups</a></strong> — Science and skepticism groups</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.sundayassembly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sunday Assembly</a></strong> — Secular congregations celebrating life ("church for people who don't do God")</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>For students</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.secularstudents.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Secular Student Alliance</a></strong> — Campus groups at 200+ universities</li>
        <li><strong><a href="https://www.campquest.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Camp Quest</a></strong> — Summer camps for freethinking families</li>
      </ul>


